# Phase 14: Stabilizing Download Manager & Navigation

This phase addresses the crash reported when clicking to view download progress. The crash is likely due to a combination of missing XAML resources and a navigation tag mismatch in the main window.

## Proposed Changes

### 1. Navigation Synchronization
#### [MODIFY] [MainWindow.xaml.cs](file:///C:/Users/Linyizhi/.gemini/GeminiLauncher/MainWindow.xaml.cs)
- Update the [NavigateToPage](file:///C:/Users/Linyizhi/.gemini/GeminiLauncher/MainWindow.xaml.cs#125-151) method to point the `download` tag to [DownloadManagerPage](file:///C:/Users/Linyizhi/.gemini/GeminiLauncher/Views/DownloadManagerPage.xaml.cs#11-16) instead of the legacy [DownloadPage](file:///C:/Users/Linyizhi/.gemini/GeminiLauncher/Views/DownloadPage.xaml.cs#5-12).

### 2. XAML Resource Fixes
#### [MODIFY] [DownloadManagerPage.xaml](file:///C:/Users/Linyizhi/.gemini/GeminiLauncher/Views/DownloadManagerPage.xaml)
- Replace non-existent `iOS26.Layer0` with `iOS26.CardLayer` or `iOS26.ContentLayer`.
- Double-check icon naming consistency (e.g., `Games24`).

### 3. Sidebar Binding Refinement
#### [MODIFY] [DownloadManagerPanel.xaml](file:///C:/Users/Linyizhi/.gemini/GeminiLauncher/Views/DownloadManagerPanel.xaml)
- Ensure the visibility binding uses the correct property and handles potential nulls gracefully.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- `dotnet build` to ensure all XAML references are statically resolvable where possible.

### Manual Verification
- Click the floating download button during an active download to ensure it navigates to the detailed manager without crashing.
- Click the "Download" item in the sidebar to verify it also leads to the correct page.
